From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-06-10
Subject: [PATCH] model_runner: 480s -> 1800s unbalanced-load timeout (cold cache)

Graft of R9700's patch 048 (their numbering; finding 2026-06-10): big-model
TP=2 loads on a cold page cache exceed upstream's 480s
UNBALANCED_MODEL_LOADING_TIMEOUT_S rank-skew window — the slower rank gets
killed mid-load. Bites 30-62 GB checkpoints when NVMe is contended (e.g.
bake-off docker I/O); directly relevant to the queued Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni
62 GB BF16 TP=2 smoke. Bump to 1800s; the timeout still catches genuinely
wedged ranks. Narrative: patches/README.md.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py b/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
index ff937dd9c..587525704 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/model_executor/model_runner.py
@@ -284,7 +284,7 @@ def add_chunked_prefix_cache_attention_backend(backend_name):
 
 
 # Detect stragger ranks in model loading
-UNBALANCED_MODEL_LOADING_TIMEOUT_S = 480  # leave more time for post data processing
+UNBALANCED_MODEL_LOADING_TIMEOUT_S = 1800  # [3090 049] cold-page-cache TP2 loads of 30-62 GB checkpoints exceed upstream 480s rank-skew window (R9700 finding); leave more time for post data processing
 
 
 logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
